<p>
<seg id=1> America and North Korea decided to hold talks on Friday to discuss further inspection of a location near Pyongyang suspected of being an underground nuclear facility. </seg>
<seg id=2> Representatives of both parties will hold a two-day talk first in New York and then in Washington. </seg>
<seg id=3> Last month similar negotiations were held in Pyongyang. </seg>
<seg id=4> At that time the negotiations were declared a failure because of demands made by North Korea. </seg>
<seg id=5> North Korea required America to provide US$300 million, in exchange for which the inspectors would be granted permission to check all related locations. </seg>
<seg id=6> Before this new round of talks, North Korea made a series of verbal attacks on the US. </seg>
</p>
